com.logimethods.connector.spark.to_nats

Class SparkToNatsConnectorPool<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.logimethods.connector.spark.to_nats.SparkToNatsConnectorPool<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractSparkToNatsStreamingConnectorPool, AbstractSparkToStandardNatsConnectorPool

    public abstract class SparkToNatsConnectorPool<T>
extends Object
    A pool of SparkToNatsConnector(s).

    That class provides a pool of Spark to NATS Connectors, which will constantly send to NATS the records belonging to a Spark Stream, such as follow: 

    SparkToNatsConnectorPool
    .newStreamingPool(clusterID)
    .withConnectionTimeout(Duration.ofSeconds(6))
    .withSubjects("subject1", "subject2")
    .withNatsURL(STAN_URL)
    .publishToNatsAsKeyValue(stream);
    Author:
    Laurent Magnin
    See Also:
    (Java based) NATS / Spark Connectors, Design Patterns for using foreachRDD, Serialized Form
